@Node "COC" "Constant calculus"

@{b}@{u}Constant calculus@{uu}@{ub}

TotalCalc is able to repeat the last operation performed. Here are some
examples:

   Example                                 Operation                Reading
   ________________________________________________________________________

   3+2.3=5.3                               3 + 2.3 =                    5.3
   6+2.3=8.3                                     6 =                    8.3


   2.3x12=27.6                            2.3 * 12 =                   27.6
   (-9)x12=-108                              9 +/- =                   -108


   17+17+17+17=68                         17 + = = =                     68


   3x6x4=72                            4 * (3 * 6) =                     72
   3x6x(-5)=-90                              5 +/- =                    -90


     56
   ­­­­­­­=2.8                  56 / (4 * (2 + 3)) =                    2.8
   4x(2+3)

     23
   ­­­­­­­=1.15                                 23 =                   1.15
   4x(2+3)


   12% of 1200=144                       12 * 1200 %                    144
   18% of 1200=216                              18 %                    216
   23% of 1200=276                              23 %                    276


   26% of 2200=572                       2200 * 26 %                    572
   26% of 3300=858                            3300 %                    858
   26% of 3800=988                            3800 %                    988


   Percentage of 30 against 192=15.625%   30 / 192 %                 15.625
   Percentage of 156 against 192=81.25%        156 %                  81.25


   If you add 600cc to a solution of    600 + 1200 %                    150
   1200cc, what is the percentage of
   the  new volume compared with the
   initial one?.................150%

   If you add 510cc to a solution of           510 %                  142.5
   1200cc, what is the percentage of
   the  new volume compared with the
   initial one?...............142.5%


   What is the percentage of decrease    138 - 150 %                     -8
   of $138 compared with $150?....-8%

   What is the percentage of decrease          129 %                    -14
   of $129 compared with $150?...-14%


@Endnode
@Node "NOT" "Notes"

@{b}@{u}Notes@{uu}@{ub}

   - TotalCalc does not care about the priority of the operators but it
     performs the operations sequentially. So the calculus '2+3*4' will be
     processed as '(2+3)*4=20' and not as '2+(3*4)=14'. Use the parentheses
     to obviate this.
   - The @{"Extras window" link "EXW"} can also be opened/closed by pressing the space
     bar.
   - You can use the cursor up and down keys to choose which independent
     memory to use.
   - Clicking on the @{"main window" link "MAW"}'s close gadget, or pressing the 'Esc'
     key, causes the user interface to be closed without quitting the
     program.


@Endnode
@Node "GUA" "Guarantee"

@{b}@{u}Guarantee@{uu}@{ub}

The program has been tested several times, but its reliability is not
guaranteed at 100%. I (@{"the author" link "AUT"}) do not consider myself responsible
for loss or damage of data as consequence of the use of the program. Use
TotalCalc at your own risk.


@Endnode
